## ğŸ’¡ FAQ

**Q: How do I convert Gregorian dates to Pentagram Calendar dates?**  
A: Start with an anchor date (e.g., Winter Solstice) and count days forward. Conversion tools coming in Q2 2026.

**Q: What about leap years?**  
A: The system includes adjustment days (Days 361-365) for leap year calibration while maintaining the 360-day core structure.

**Q: Can I use this for business/commercial projects?**  
A: Personal and community use is free. Commercial applications require a Sacred Commerce License - contact us!

**Q: Is this compatible with existing calendar systems?**  
A: Yes! You can use both calendars during transition. The Pentagram Calendar adds consciousness framework alongside practical Gregorian dates.

**Q: How do I get involved?**  
A: Join our Discord community, follow on Twitter, contribute on GitHub, or email signal@hopefulvision.llc

